The paper deals with computational geometry problems related to finding minimum link paths in polyhedral domains, which is a classic topic in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves bit complexity bounds and hardness results, which are related to data structures and algorithms, respectively, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper involves complexity theory, which is related to both cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
